<div class="container">
<div id="new-project">
  <table class="new">
  <%= form_for :project, url: user_projects_path(user_id: @user.id) do |f| %>
  <tr><td>
    <%= f.label "Title" %></td><td>
    <%= f.text_field :title %></td>
    </tr><tr>
    <td><%= f.label "Domain" %></td>
    <td><%= f.text_field :domain %></td>
    </tr><tr>
    <td><%= f.label "Description" %></td>
    <td><%= f.text_field :description %></td>
    </tr><tr>
    <td><%= f.submit "Get Report" %></td>
    </tr>
  <% end %>
  </form>
</table>
</div>
<h3>Instructions: </h3>
<ol>
  <li>Open up the base HTML document for your website.</li>
  <li>Copy the code below.</li>
  <li>Paste the code in the "head" section of page.</li>
  <li>Replace "YOUR_DOMAIN_NAME_HERE" with the domain you signed up with.</li>
</ol>
<p>That's it. Once you have your site live, your Pixie Report will begin automatically updating.</p>

<div id="xmp">
  <xmp>
    <script>var domain = YOUR_DOMAIN_NAME_HERE</script>
    <script src="https://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/2.1.3/jquery.min.js"></script>
    <script src="http://triathloncodes.github.io/PixiePackage.js"></script>
  </xmp>
  </div>
  <p><strong>You will need to make one change.</strong> On the first line, where you see "YOUR_DOMAIN_NAME_HERE" replace with your domain name. It is important that this is exactly the same as the one you sign up with.</p>
</div>
